  "texts": [
    "The study also addressed the educational gap in taxonomic training by creating an extensive image library and digital taxonomic tools available through the Endless Forams online portal and a Zooniverse project (Hsiang et al. 2019) (h t t p s: / / g i t h u b.",
    "c o m / a h s i a n g / f o r a m -c l a s s i fi e r).",
    "Additionally, the research highlighted the classifier's advantage in consistency and bias mitigation over human classifiers, suggesting that expanding sample sizes and enhancing data quality could improve DL outcomes.",
    "However, the study does rely on expert-generated labels, which introduces potential biases into the training data, particularly in species with low representation, thereby affecting the model's ability to generalize across less common species.",
    "In a study by de Lima et al. (2019), CNN models are specifically applied to classify images of Foraminifera, alongside other geological images such as core samples, petrographic thin sections, and rock specimens."
  ]
